The Federal High Courts in Osogbo, Osun State and Ado-Ekiti in Ekiti State have convicted six Yahoo Boys over fraudulent impersonation. A statement by the Head, Media and Publicity, Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Wilson Uwujaren which was made available to reporters disclosed that “Ahmed Abiona, Owoade Elijah, Oriade Oluwatobiloba, Usman Shehu, and Waris Adeyemo were prosecuted before Justice Nathaniel Ayo-Emmanuel of the Federal High Court, Osogbo, Osun State, while David Fatunla Taiwo (aka Jeff Wood), was prosecuted before Justice Babs Kuewunmi of the Federal High Court, Ado-Ekiti. He noted that they pleaded guilty to their respective one-count charge and were convicted accordingly. “Abiona, Adeyemo and Shehu bagged four months each, Owoade three months, while Oriade was sentenced to five months imprisonment. Taiwo was slammed with 20 months imprisonment.”   Two burnt, 30 houses destroyed in gas-laden tanker explosion     Sylvester Oromoni: Dowen College’s founder, board quit     Youths set two robbery suspects ablaze in Imo   Read Also: Ogun declares war on kidnappers, Yahoo boys - Advertisement - “The court also ordered the defendants to restitute their victims. Oriade is to restitute his victim to the tune of $590. He was equally ordered to forfeit an iPhone XR, one Samsung S5 mobile phone and one Acer Laptop to the Federal Government. “Ahmed is to restitute to one Michael Johnson the sum of $500 and further forfeit the sum of N3, 013,007.39 found in his bank accounts. Adeyemo was ordered to return the sum of $300 to one Peter Decker and forfeit one iPhone 11 Pro Max to the Federal Government. Shehu is to restitute his victim for the sum of $400 and forfeit one Samsung Galaxy S8 to the Federal Government. Owoade was ordered to restitute his victim for the sum of $300 and forfeit an iPhone 6 mobile phone to the Federal Government. Taiwo was ordered to restitute his victim, Joanne K. Thornhill, the sum of £450 through the Federal Government.”